The detection efficiency for such a beam is found to be $\eta = 0.12$ showing that the cross-talk between different modes is low.

We have shown that in a projective LG measurement, maximum possible detection efficiency can be achieved for all the modes simultaneously. In particular, higher-order OAM modes can also be detected with high efficiency comparable to lower order modes. 

